history.content:
For all CS grad course, before you can enroll you need the instructor to communicate with me that you have permission to do so.  Generally, CS faculty don't do this until after phase 1 and 2 are over and they can asses if they are able to accommodate all interested grad students first.

For EE grad courses, it is basically the same process though some faculty approve before the phases have ended. Please forward the EE faculty confirmations to me. Thanks!

children.subject: Please first get permission from the instructor and then forward the email to Michael-David Sasson (CS classes) or me (EE classes). Depending on the enrollment of the class, you may need to wait until the end of Phase II to be enrolled.

Graduate classes

How does one sign up for grad classes in the new system? Do we talk to the professor to get the required permission code or our ESS advisor or...?

I got the following message:

Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements.
